item.description:
@Spades wrote:

[quote=“killah1333, post:13, topic:337679”][quote author=Kryptix link=topic=434081.msg3188531#msg3188531 date=1272005198]
ICodeForFame and I tried setting RSCD up on his machine but he’s not behind a router and wouldn’t let any external connections come in on port 80. It took us about an hour to find out where on earth his htdocs/www folder actually was as he had installed WAMP and xampp several times. In the end we found the htdocs folder for xampp in his My Received Files. His My Documents folder has over 12gB of RSC/RS2 ‘sources’ with literally every name you could possibly imagine. XboxScape, LeetScape, DonstaScape, you name it… When in Task Manage we also saw that he had over 10 Java applications running so he’s probably keylogged/virused up to the sky and back. Whilst we was on TeamViewer with him he accepted and ran a ‘source’ that someone sent him over MSN who had only just added him which proved he really does accept and run absolutely anything.

To top it off, I never saw his CPU usage under 95%. His PC specs were awful too with 1gB of RAM. I really, really don’t think it’s the best environment to host a server.

PS. He’s 15.
